      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The certainty of the end is a very heavy anchor, and it's understandable why that makes everything else feel pointless. When everything is temporary, the only thing that truly becomes available is the *now*. Instead of fighting the end, perhaps you could lean into the raw, fleeting intensity of what is happening right now. Let the weight be a focus, not just a burden, and see what that feels like.",
      "source": "target",
